          <h2>Introduction to Indian Budget</h2>
          <p>The Indian Budget is an annual financial statement presented by the Government of India in the Parliament. It outlines the government's revenue and expenditure for the upcoming fiscal year, along with policy initiatives and plans for various sectors of the economy.</p>

          <h2>Key Highlights</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Revenue and Expenditure Allocation</li>
            <li>Tax Reforms and Amendments</li>
            <li>Infrastructure Development Plans</li>
            <li>Social Welfare and Healthcare Initiatives</li>
            <li>Economic Growth Projections</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Impact on Various Sectors</h2>
          <p>The Indian Budget has a significant impact on various sectors of the economy, including:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Agriculture</li>
            <li>Manufacturing and Industries</li>
            <li>Information Technology</li>
            <li>Education and Skill Development</li>
            <li>Healthcare</li>
            <li>Infrastructure</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Conclusion</h2>
          <p>The Indian Budget is a crucial instrument for economic planning and development in the country. It provides insights into the government's fiscal policies and priorities, which directly affect different sectors and the overall growth of the economy.</p>
